{"id":16543,"date":"2024-02-19T09:24:00","date_gmt":"2022-11-19T03:54:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=16543"},"modified":"2022-12-26T15:47:28","modified_gmt":"2022-12-26T10:17:28","slug":"small-kitchen-organisation-on-budget","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/small-kitchen-organisation-on-budget\/","title":{"rendered":"Small Kitchen Organisation Ideas: Say Goodbye To Clutter With These Smart Solutions"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Even the smallest kitchen can be organised in a space-saving way such that it is both stylish and functional. Read our small kitchen storage ideas to get inspired.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you have limited space in the kitchen, you may often struggle to find what you need at the right time, thereby creating unnecessary chaos at the time of cooking. Hence, you need to make optimal use of every inch of the kitchen so that you can work efficiently and hassle-free.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Trust us, once you check out our smart small <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">kitchen design<\/a> and storage ideas like the small kitchen shelf organiser and small kitchen storage racks, you\u2019ll know all about making your kitchen feel twice as big and keeping it spick-and-span.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"2018\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"small kitchen storage ideas and How to organise a small kitchen\" class=\"wp-image-39451\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen-140x300.jpg 140w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen-477x1024.jpg 477w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen-768x1649.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen-715x1536.jpg 715w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/19141402\/how-to-organise-small-kitchen-150x322.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, let\u2019s dive into our <strong>small kitchen storage ideas<\/strong> and see which ones inspire you for your next kitchen makeover project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Kitchen Storage Solution With Open And Closed Units<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small kitchen storage idea is a creative mix of open and closed storage units. The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/open-shelving-kitchen-ideas\/\">open shelves<\/a> let you keep frequently-used items within arm\u2019s reach like jams, sauces and spices. Precious China plates, dishes and mugs are stacked in a closed cabinet with a bi-fold lift-up shutter so that they are nearly invisible when not in use. It gives a streamlined and sophisticated feel to the kitchen. The pull-out storage trays help you utilise the awkward corners of the kitchen efficiently by helping you store bulkier items like appliances and pots\/pans.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110359\/small-kitchen-organization-with-open-and-closed-units.jpg\" alt=\"small kitchen storage ideas with open and closed units offers an easy-to-use experience\" class=\"wp-image-39446\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110359\/small-kitchen-organization-with-open-and-closed-units.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110359\/small-kitchen-organization-with-open-and-closed-units-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110359\/small-kitchen-organization-with-open-and-closed-units-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110359\/small-kitchen-organization-with-open-and-closed-units-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A pull-down table offers extra workspace<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Up your kitchen organisation game with our storage ideas\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17142233\/up-your-kitchen-organisation-game-with-our-storage-ideas.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Tall Glass Pantry Is A Great Storage Idea For Small Kitchens<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An integrated tall pantry with a transparent folding door is perfect for organising a small kitchen. It is quite practical because the shelves are placed at different heights to accommodate differently-sized pots, mugs and non-perishable food items. Give your kitchen a modern makeover by integrating appliances such as the oven and the microwave into your kitchen cabinet panel so that they look like a single and complete unit. Install accent lighting in the small kitchen storage cupboard so that you can clearly view the placement of the kitchen items.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110326\/how-to-organize-small-kitchen-with-tall-glass-pantry.jpg\" alt=\"How to organize a small kitchen with a tall glass pantry\" class=\"wp-image-39441\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110326\/how-to-organize-small-kitchen-with-tall-glass-pantry.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110326\/how-to-organize-small-kitchen-with-tall-glass-pantry-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110326\/how-to-organize-small-kitchen-with-tall-glass-pantry-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110326\/how-to-organize-small-kitchen-with-tall-glass-pantry-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Add some greenery with potted plants<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Optimise Available Space In A Small Kitchen With A Side Cabinet<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Doesn\u2019t this tall cabinet on the side look unique? The interesting part of this kitchen storage cabinet is that it looks aesthetically appealing and part of the structure when the door is closed but magical and highly functional when it is opened. You can either display plates and soup bowls in there or store bottles, juice tetra packs and perishable knick-knacks. The combination of lavender and beige in the kitchen theme adds a subtle charm to the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110347\/small-kitchen-organization-ideas-with-side-cabinet.jpg\" alt=\"small kitchen storage ideas to optimize the available space with a side cabinet\" class=\"wp-image-39444\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110347\/small-kitchen-organization-ideas-with-side-cabinet.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110347\/small-kitchen-organization-ideas-with-side-cabinet-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110347\/small-kitchen-organization-ideas-with-side-cabinet-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110347\/small-kitchen-organization-ideas-with-side-cabinet-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Enhance the kitchen\u2019s beauty with a piece of art<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Baskets Are A Handy Storage Solution For Small Kitchens<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When organised well, designated kitchen storage units inject an element of style and elegance into the kitchen. A pair of rattan baskets are perfect for small kitchen storage. They come in handy to store produce like fresh fruits and vegetables so that they are constantly ventilated. You can easily access cooking items like spices and condiments from the open corner cabinets above, thereby saving you ample time. A small kitchen island and a ceiling-mounted glass holder will also be quite the stunner.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110406\/small-space-kitchen-organization-with-baskets.jpg\" alt=\"Small space kitchen organization with baskets are handy storage solutions\" class=\"wp-image-39447\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110406\/small-space-kitchen-organization-with-baskets.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110406\/small-space-kitchen-organization-with-baskets-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110406\/small-space-kitchen-organization-with-baskets-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110406\/small-space-kitchen-organization-with-baskets-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Group kitchen items into clusters for easy access<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Storage Shelves With Sliding Doors In A Small Kitchen<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small kitchen storage idea of customised shelves with sliding doors does wonders for your kitchen. It does not disturb your kitchen workspace as compared to closed cabinets with pull-open doors, and also adds visual depth to the space. Transfer all your dried foods, cereals, nuts, sugar, pulses, flours, etc. into labelled transparent containers as it will make it much easier to locate what you need and you\u2019ll also be able to see when the kitchen essentials are running low.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110354\/small-kitchen-organization-storage-shelves-with-sliding-doors.jpg\" alt=\"Small kitchen organization storage shelves with sliding doors\" class=\"wp-image-39445\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110354\/small-kitchen-organization-storage-shelves-with-sliding-doors.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110354\/small-kitchen-organization-storage-shelves-with-sliding-doors-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110354\/small-kitchen-organization-storage-shelves-with-sliding-doors-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110354\/small-kitchen-organization-storage-shelves-with-sliding-doors-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Follow \u2018first in, first out\u2019 method to avoid clutter<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Kitchen Storage Idea For Small Kitchens With A Spice Rack<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to display the frequently-used kitchen spices and condiments for cooking is by using a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-spice-rack-ideas\/\">compact spice rack<\/a> or shelves set. Stacking them randomly in a cupboard without any logical order will only lead to confusion and chaos. So, this is where printed labels come to the rescue. Designate a specific shelf for specific kinds of cooking-related items for better and more effective organisation like all the oils on one shelf, tea and coffee ingredients on another shelf.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110334\/small-kitchen-organisation-with-spice-rack.jpg\" alt=\"Small kitchen storage ideas with spice racks is the easiest way to display the frequently-used stuff\" class=\"wp-image-39442\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110334\/small-kitchen-organisation-with-spice-rack.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110334\/small-kitchen-organisation-with-spice-rack-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110334\/small-kitchen-organisation-with-spice-rack-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/19110334\/small-kitchen-organisation-with-spice-rack-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Use a wall-mounted holder for cooking spoons<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope these <em>small kitchen storage ideas<\/em> will help you organise your cooking space in no time and within a reasonable budget. Contact <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe <\/a>if you want our expert team\u2019s guidance to maximise space in your small kitchen. Good luck!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>